WEBVTT

00:03.169 --> 00:04.971
- ♪ TIMMY IS AN AVERAGE KID ♪

00:05.038 --> 00:07.974
♪ THAT NO ONE UNDERSTANDS ♪

00:08.041 --> 00:11.578
♪ MOM AND DAD AND VICKY
ALWAYS GIVING HIM COMMANDS ♪

00:11.644 --> 00:13.246
- BED, TWERP!

00:13.313 --> 00:15.215
- ♪ THE DOOM AND GLOOM
UP IN HIS ROOM ♪

00:15.281 --> 00:17.684
♪ IS BROKEN INSTANTLY ♪

00:17.751 --> 00:20.153
♪ BY HIS MAGIC LITTLE FISH
WHO GRANT HIS EVERY WISH ♪

00:20.220 --> 00:21.588
♪ 'CAUSE IN REALITY ♪

00:21.654 --> 00:23.623
♪ THEY ARE HIS ODDPARENTS ♪

00:23.690 --> 00:24.991
♪ FAIRLY ODDPARENTS ♪

00:25.058 --> 00:25.959
- WANDS AND WINGS.

00:26.025 --> 00:27.727
- FLOAT-Y CROWN-Y THINGS.

00:27.794 --> 00:30.163
- ♪ ODDPARENTS,
FAIRLY ODDPARENTS ♪

00:30.230 --> 00:32.564
♪ REALLY MOD, PEA POD,
BUFF BOD, HOT ROD ♪

00:32.631 --> 00:35.135
- OBTUSE, RUBBER GOOSE,
GREEN MOOSE, GUAVA JUICE,

00:35.201 --> 00:39.038
GIANT SNAKE, BIRTHDAY CAKE,
LARGE FRIES, CHOCOLATE SHAKE!

00:39.105 --> 00:41.307
- ♪ ODDPARENTS,
FAIRLY ODDPARENTS ♪

00:41.374 --> 00:43.209
{\an8}♪ IT FLIPS YOUR LID
WHEN YOU ARE THE KID ♪

00:43.276 --> 00:44.911
{\an8}♪ WITH FAIRLY ODDPARENTS ♪

00:44.978 --> 00:46.146
{\an8}- YEAH, RIGHT.

00:59.559 --> 01:02.328
- TIMOTHY TIBERIUS TURNER,
HURRY UP.

01:02.395 --> 01:05.799
THE SCHOOL BUS WILL BE HERE
ANY MINUTE.

01:05.865 --> 01:07.133
- TIMMY!

01:07.200 --> 01:09.602
TIMMY, YOUR MOM'S CALLING YOU.

01:09.669 --> 01:11.671
- HANG ON;
I'M ABOUT TO BEAT GATOR LADY

01:11.738 --> 01:14.007
IN <i> ALIEN HILLBILLY</i>
<i>DEATH RACE 2000.</i>

01:14.073 --> 01:15.742
[growling crazily]

01:15.809 --> 01:17.410
[metal clanking]

01:17.477 --> 01:18.411
[drill noise]

01:18.478 --> 01:19.446
- NO!

01:19.512 --> 01:22.248
YOUR MIDDLE NAME IS TIBERIUS?

01:22.315 --> 01:23.616
[tires screeching]

01:23.683 --> 01:26.686
- AH!

01:26.753 --> 01:29.122
- TIMMY, YOU LOOK LIKE YOU'VE
BEEN RUN OVER

01:29.189 --> 01:31.157
BY ALIEN HILLBILLIES.

01:31.224 --> 01:34.394
NOW, CATCH YOUR BREAKFAST.

01:34.461 --> 01:37.464
MY DAY IS TOUGH ENOUGH
WITHOUT YOU GETTING BLOWN UP.

01:37.530 --> 01:39.032
-<i> HER</i> DAY IS TOUGH?
HA!

01:39.098 --> 01:42.068
- AW, SPORT, YOUR MOTHER
IS JUST VERY BUSY.

01:42.135 --> 01:44.704
IT'S NOT EASY BEING A MOM.

01:44.771 --> 01:46.239
- COMPARED TO MY LIFE,
IT SURE IS.

01:46.306 --> 01:47.540
[baby giggling]

01:47.607 --> 01:50.677
MOM HAS NO IDEA WHAT I GO
THROUGH EVERY DAY.

01:50.743 --> 01:51.878
BULLIES BEAT ME.

01:51.945 --> 01:56.115
TEACHERS FAIL ME.

01:56.182 --> 01:59.118
IT'S WAY EASIER BEING A MOM
THAN A TEN-YEAR-OLD.

01:59.185 --> 02:00.753
- CARE TO PUT YOUR MONEY
WHERE YOUR MOUTH IS?

02:00.820 --> 02:02.422
OR ARE YOU TOO CHICKEN?

02:02.489 --> 02:04.657
[baby giggling]

02:04.724 --> 02:07.160
[loud banging]

02:07.227 --> 02:08.595
- POOF-POOF!

02:08.661 --> 02:10.096
- I'D TOTALLY BET YOU.

02:10.163 --> 02:12.565
I JUST DON'T HAVE ANY MONEY
'CAUSE I'M A KID.

02:12.632 --> 02:14.000
- [makes chicken noise]

02:14.067 --> 02:16.069
- THAT LAME ATTEMPT
AT A CHICKEN NOISE

02:16.135 --> 02:17.604
IS NOT GONNA WORK ON...

02:17.670 --> 02:20.640
- [making chicken noise]

02:20.707 --> 02:21.908
- YOU'RE ON!

02:21.975 --> 02:23.643
- ALL RIGHT, A BET.

02:23.710 --> 02:25.545
TIMMY HAS TO BE HIS MOM
FOR A WHOLE DAY,

02:25.612 --> 02:27.313
AND HIS MOM HAS TO BE TIMMY.

02:27.380 --> 02:29.015
OOH!
I KNOW.

02:29.082 --> 02:31.150
IF TIMMY WINS,
WANDA HAS TO LIVE AS A CHICKEN

02:31.217 --> 02:32.418
FOR A WHOLE WEEK.

02:32.485 --> 02:33.453
- I LIKE IT.

02:33.520 --> 02:34.754
- BUT IF TIMMY DOESN'T SUCCEED

02:34.821 --> 02:36.389
AS MOM FOR A WHOLE DAY,

02:36.456 --> 02:38.291
HE GETS NO MAGIC FOR A WEEK.

02:38.358 --> 02:39.559
- WHAT?

02:39.626 --> 02:40.593
- B'GAWK!

02:40.660 --> 02:42.462
- DEAL!

02:42.529 --> 02:44.731
- I JUST CAN'T SEEM
TO GET THROUGH TO TIMMY.

02:44.797 --> 02:48.001
MAYBE THIS BOOK ON PARENTING
WRITTEN BY MR. CROCKER'S MOM

02:48.067 --> 02:50.003
CAN HELP ME DEAL WITH HIM.

02:50.069 --> 02:53.706
<i>HOW TO RAISE YOUR CHILD SO HE</i>
<i>DOESN'T TURN OUT LIKE MINE.</i>

02:53.773 --> 02:55.141
CHAPTER ONE:

02:55.208 --> 02:59.112
TO UNDERSTAND YOUR CHILD,
VISUALIZE HIS POINT OF VIEW.

02:59.178 --> 03:00.980
I AM TIMMY.

03:01.047 --> 03:02.482
I AM TIMMY.

03:02.549 --> 03:04.250
I AM TIMMY.

03:04.317 --> 03:05.885
[fanfare]

03:05.952 --> 03:08.154
[zapping noise]

03:13.960 --> 03:17.497
WOW, I'M REALLY GOOD
AT VISUALIZING.

03:17.564 --> 03:18.631
[chimes]

03:18.698 --> 03:20.867
- WHOA, I'M ACTUALLY MOM.

03:20.934 --> 03:23.136
I THINK I'LL GO DO SOMETHING
TOTALLY MOM-LIKE.

03:23.202 --> 03:24.537
I'M GONNA YELL AT ME.

03:24.604 --> 03:26.306
TIMMY!

03:29.409 --> 03:31.444
GOOD MORNING, TIMMY.

03:31.511 --> 03:33.947
- GOOD MORNING...MOM.

03:34.013 --> 03:35.915
OH, SO FAR, SO GOOD.

03:35.982 --> 03:37.116
NEXT STEP:

03:39.953 --> 03:40.887
[horn honking]

03:40.954 --> 03:42.088
THE SCHOOL BUS.

03:42.155 --> 03:44.290
PERFECT,
I'M OFF TO TIMMY'S SCHOOL.

03:44.357 --> 03:46.593
I MEAN, MY SCHOOL.

03:46.659 --> 03:48.361
- MOM TOTALLY THINKS SHE'S ME.

03:48.428 --> 03:49.362
AWESOME.

03:49.429 --> 03:51.698
HELLO, TOY STORE.

03:51.764 --> 03:53.666
THIS IS TIMMY...'S MOM.

03:53.733 --> 03:55.602
I'D LIKE TO ORDER A BUNCH
OF VIDEO GAMES

03:55.668 --> 03:57.904
BECAUSE I'VE RECENTLY BECOME
AN ADULT WOMAN.

03:57.971 --> 04:00.807
PLEASE CHARGE THEM TO MY
ADULT WOMAN CREDIT CARD.

04:00.873 --> 04:02.609
[fanfare]

04:02.675 --> 04:03.610
SWEET!

04:03.676 --> 04:04.611
NOW I CAN KICK BACK

04:04.677 --> 04:06.579
AND PLAY VIDEO GAMES ALL DAY.

04:06.646 --> 04:08.681
- GUESS AGAIN, MOM.

04:08.748 --> 04:10.883
READ YOUR DAY PLANNER.

04:10.950 --> 04:12.151
[papers flapping]

04:12.218 --> 04:14.253
- WHOA, ALL THESE NOTES
ARE FOR CHORES?

04:14.320 --> 04:15.888
YOU GOT TO BE--
- B'GAWK!

04:15.955 --> 04:17.656
- I MEAN, YAY, CHORES.

04:17.724 --> 04:19.692
FIRST UP, CLEAN TIMMY'S ROOM.

04:19.759 --> 04:21.094
WELL, THAT'S EASY.

04:21.160 --> 04:22.562
I WISH MY ROOM WAS CLEAN.

04:22.629 --> 04:24.731
- AW, SORRY, SPORT.

04:24.797 --> 04:27.734
YOU'RE MOM NOW,
AND SHE DOESN'T HAVE FAIRIES.

04:27.800 --> 04:29.469
TOO BAD, HUH?

04:29.535 --> 04:30.737
- NO WORRIES, WANDA.

04:30.803 --> 04:32.572
I CAN TOTALLY CLEAN MY OWN ROOM.

04:32.639 --> 04:34.741
BESIDES,
I'M NOT THAT MESSY, ANYWAY.

04:34.807 --> 04:36.042
WHOA.

04:36.109 --> 04:38.244
[weird throaty sound]

04:38.311 --> 04:39.278
- YA-A-AH!

04:39.345 --> 04:41.014
THE TRASH MONSTER'S GOT ME.

04:41.080 --> 04:43.049
DOWN, MR. SQUIGGLES, DOWN!

04:43.116 --> 04:45.018
- MAYBE YOU'D LIKE
TO END THE BET?

04:45.084 --> 04:46.185
- NOT A CHANCE.

04:46.252 --> 04:47.954
STAYING HOME AND CLEANING
AS MOM

04:48.021 --> 04:49.522
STILL BEATS BEING ME.

04:49.589 --> 04:51.090
AND SPEAKING OF BEATINGS,

04:51.157 --> 04:53.893
I BET MY MOM'S HAVING FUN
ON THE BUS.

04:55.628 --> 04:58.364
- TURNER,
WELCOME TO CHEZ FRANCIS.

04:58.431 --> 05:00.633
TODAY'S SPECIALS
ARE THE BROKEN LEG OF LAMB

05:00.700 --> 05:01.934
AND THE CRACKED RIBS.

05:02.001 --> 05:03.136
AND FOR DESSERT...

05:03.202 --> 05:04.737
POUND CAKE.

05:04.804 --> 05:05.938
- OH, LET ME GUESS.

05:06.005 --> 05:08.541
YOU'RE THE ANGRY SCHOOL BULLY.

05:08.608 --> 05:09.909
WHEN PEOPLE ARE ANGRY,

05:09.976 --> 05:13.179
IT USUALLY MEANS
THEY'VE HAD A DREAM CRUSHED.

05:13.246 --> 05:17.150
DO YOU HAVE A CRUSHED DREAM,
LARGE GRAY BOY?

05:17.216 --> 05:20.253
- WELL, I HAVE ALWAYS WANTED
TO BE AN INTERPRETIVE DANCER.

05:20.319 --> 05:21.287
- WONDERFUL.

05:21.354 --> 05:23.256
LET'S DANCE RIGHT NOW.

05:23.322 --> 05:26.893
[lush orchestral music]

05:26.959 --> 05:28.027
- I'M BLOSSOMING.

05:28.094 --> 05:30.997
I FEEL SO FREE!

05:31.064 --> 05:33.066
[electronic beeping]

05:33.132 --> 05:34.634
[together]
SPRINGTIME!

05:34.701 --> 05:36.703
all: SPRINGTIME!

05:36.769 --> 05:39.205
- THERE,
MY ROOM IS FINALLY CLEAN.

05:39.272 --> 05:41.174
TIME TO RELAX WITH A COMIC BOOK.

05:41.240 --> 05:42.575
- NO RELAXING YET.

05:42.642 --> 05:44.377
NEXT UP IN YOUR MOM'S PLANNER:

05:44.444 --> 05:46.179
LAUNDRY AND DISHES.

05:46.245 --> 05:47.947
[light splash]

05:48.014 --> 05:50.583
[weird throaty noise]

05:50.650 --> 05:52.785
- AH!
NOT AGAIN, MR. SQUIGGLES.

05:52.852 --> 05:54.787
I ALREADY GAVE YOU MY LIVER.

05:54.854 --> 05:55.855
- COSMO, NO!

05:55.922 --> 05:58.191
[loud clattering]

05:58.257 --> 05:59.392
[phone ringing]

05:59.459 --> 06:00.426
- HELLO?

06:00.493 --> 06:01.394
- HI, HONEY.

06:01.461 --> 06:03.196
BOY, YOU SOUND A LOT LIKE TIMMY.

06:03.262 --> 06:05.064
HEY, LISTEN,
I FORGOT MY LUNCH,

06:05.131 --> 06:06.799
AND I'M TOO BUSY WORKING
TO GO OUT.

06:06.866 --> 06:08.668
MAN, THAT TIMMY'S A GOOD DANCER.

06:08.735 --> 06:09.669
CAN YOU BRING IT TO ME?

06:09.736 --> 06:11.304
- NO WAY, I'VE GOT A LOT TO--

06:11.370 --> 06:12.371
- B'GAWK!

06:12.438 --> 06:13.372
B-B-B-B'GAWK!

06:13.439 --> 06:14.674
- OOH-HOO!

06:14.741 --> 06:16.442
ARE THERE CHICKENS RUNNING
AROUND THE HOUSE?

06:16.509 --> 06:18.878
FRY ME UP ONE OF THOSE.

06:18.945 --> 06:21.581
- NOT SO EASY
JUGGLING ALL THE THINGS

06:21.647 --> 06:24.016
A MOM HAS TO JUGGLE,
IS IT, SPORT?

06:24.083 --> 06:25.184
- NICE TRY, WANDA.

06:25.251 --> 06:27.420
BUT I'VE GOT IT ALL
UNDER CONTROL.

06:27.487 --> 06:29.589
[upbeat jazzy music]

06:29.655 --> 06:30.757
[dishes clattering]

06:30.823 --> 06:32.291
- UH-OH-OH-OH.

06:34.794 --> 06:36.429
- SEE?
UNDER CONTROL.

06:36.496 --> 06:37.897
NOW, IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME,

06:37.964 --> 06:40.666
I'VE GOT TO BRING LUNCH
TO MY LOVING HUSBAND.

06:40.733 --> 06:43.636
NOW PLEASE PRETEND
I NEVER SAID THAT.

06:43.703 --> 06:45.138
[loud gurgling]

06:45.204 --> 06:48.040
[bell ringing]

06:48.107 --> 06:49.575
- TURNER!
"F"!

06:49.642 --> 06:51.410
- AH!

06:51.477 --> 06:53.079
YOU KNOW, MR. CROCKER,

06:53.146 --> 06:54.647
PEOPLE WHO ARE HARD ON OTHERS

06:54.714 --> 06:57.617
ARE USUALLY EVEN HARDER
ON THEMSELVES.

06:57.683 --> 06:59.619
DO YOU GIVE YOURSELF "F"s TOO?

06:59.685 --> 07:01.521
- YOU'VE BEEN READING
MOTHER'S PARENTING BOOK,

07:01.587 --> 07:03.823
THE ONE SHE WAS TOO BUSY WRITING
TO RAISE ME.

07:03.890 --> 07:05.525
NORMALLY I'D GIVE YOU
ANOTHER "F" FOR THAT,

07:05.591 --> 07:07.693
BUT SUDDENLY I WANT TO...

07:07.760 --> 07:09.295
TELL YOU ABOUT
MY EMPTY CHILDHOOD.

07:09.362 --> 07:11.397
- THERE, THERE, MR. CROCKER.

07:11.464 --> 07:13.966
WHY DON'T YOU DANCE
YOUR PAIN AWAY?

07:14.033 --> 07:14.934
[lush orchestra music]

07:15.001 --> 07:16.435
SPRINGTIME!

07:16.502 --> 07:17.970
- SPRINGTIME!

07:18.037 --> 07:20.907
[people screaming]

07:22.508 --> 07:23.876
[engine revving]

07:23.943 --> 07:24.944
- HANG ON.

07:25.011 --> 07:26.679
I GOT TO SHAKE THESE COPPERS.

07:26.746 --> 07:29.148
[bell dinging]

07:29.215 --> 07:31.751
[all shouting]

07:31.818 --> 07:33.986
[loud bang]
WE'RE HERE.

07:34.053 --> 07:35.488
- THANKS, HONEY.

07:35.555 --> 07:37.089
I WANT TO SHOW YOU MY GRATITUDE

07:37.156 --> 07:39.158
WITH A BIG, WET,
SLOPPY, SMOOCHY,

07:39.225 --> 07:40.960
EUROPEAN-STYLE KISS.

07:41.027 --> 07:42.695
- WHAT?

07:42.762 --> 07:44.597
[teeth chattering]

07:44.664 --> 07:46.899
- LA-LA-LA-LA-LA-LA-LA-LA.

07:46.966 --> 07:47.867
[buzzing noise]

07:47.934 --> 07:48.968
[smooching]

07:49.035 --> 07:50.837
- I WISH I HAD
AN ELECTRIC EEL.

07:50.903 --> 07:52.305
- WELL, YOU CAN'T USE MAGIC.

07:52.371 --> 07:54.173
BUT LUCKY FOR YOU,
I ALWAYS KEEP AN ELECTRIC EEL

07:54.240 --> 07:56.075
IN MY POCKET FOR EMERGENCIES.

07:56.142 --> 07:57.977
[intense zapping noise]

07:58.044 --> 07:59.045
[smooch]

07:59.111 --> 08:02.748
[intense zapping and shouting]

08:02.815 --> 08:03.749
- DEH!

08:03.816 --> 08:04.984
AFTER ALL THESE YEARS,

08:05.051 --> 08:06.652
WE STILL HAVE THAT SPARK.

08:06.719 --> 08:08.988
KISS ME AGAIN!
KISS ME AGAIN!

08:09.055 --> 08:10.690
[tires screeching]

08:10.756 --> 08:11.691
[people screaming]

08:11.757 --> 08:12.725
[loud crash]

08:12.792 --> 08:14.126
- I SURE HOPE MY MOM IS HAVING

08:14.193 --> 08:16.162
AS BAD A DAY AS ME.

08:16.229 --> 08:18.731
- DON'T EVEN WASTE A GREETING,
TIMMY TURNER.

08:18.798 --> 08:20.600
I'M NEVER GOING TO TALK TO--

08:20.666 --> 08:22.935
- OOH, I LOVE YOUR SHOES.

08:23.002 --> 08:24.003
- YOU DO?

08:24.070 --> 08:25.037
- OOH, AND YOUR DRESS

08:25.104 --> 08:26.839
REALLY BRINGS OUT YOUR EYES.

08:26.906 --> 08:29.542
- WOW, TELL ME WHAT ELSE
YOU LOVE ABOUT ME.

08:29.609 --> 08:32.678
- ONLY IF I CAN BRAID
YOUR GORGEOUS HAIR.

08:32.745 --> 08:33.712
- TIMMY TURNER,

08:33.779 --> 08:36.015
YOU'RE WONDERFUL.

08:36.082 --> 08:37.482
[tinkling sound]

08:37.549 --> 08:39.018
[together]
SPRINGTIME!

08:39.085 --> 08:40.953
{\an5}[together]
SPRINGTIME!

08:41.020 --> 08:43.256
- UGH, WHY ARE WE AT THE MALL?

08:43.322 --> 08:45.491
- IT'S TIME FOR BARGAIN HUNTING,
SPORT.

08:45.558 --> 08:47.159
- CLOTHES SHOPPING?

08:47.226 --> 08:48.394
BUT THAT'S BORING.

08:48.461 --> 08:50.696
- NOT THE WAY YOUR MOM DOES IT.

08:50.763 --> 08:52.932
[rock music]

08:52.999 --> 08:53.933
WHEN THE WHISTLE BLOWS,

08:54.000 --> 08:56.068
RUN FOR THE SALES BINS.

08:56.135 --> 08:57.403
- AND WATCH OUT FOR MRS. HEMPLE.

08:57.470 --> 08:58.638
SHE'S A BITER.

08:58.704 --> 09:01.007
- [growling angrily]

09:01.073 --> 09:02.008
[whistle blows]

09:02.074 --> 09:03.509
[engines revving]

09:03.576 --> 09:05.011
[tires screeching]

09:05.077 --> 09:06.379
- GO FOR THE BARGAINS, TIMMY.

09:06.445 --> 09:08.681
SLACKS AT THREE O'CLOCK.

09:10.316 --> 09:11.284
- AH!

09:11.350 --> 09:13.719
- [cackling]

09:13.786 --> 09:15.588
- UGH.

09:15.655 --> 09:18.758
- GO FOR NEW UNDERWEAR, TIMMY.

09:18.824 --> 09:21.360
[women shouting]

09:26.866 --> 09:27.867
- GOT 'EM!

09:27.934 --> 09:29.669
- THOSE ARE SOCKS.

09:29.735 --> 09:30.836
- CLOSE ENOUGH.

09:30.903 --> 09:32.672
[tires screeching]

09:32.738 --> 09:36.809
NOW HURRY TO THE CHECKOUT.

09:36.876 --> 09:38.144
[metal clanking]

09:38.210 --> 09:39.178
- AH!

09:39.245 --> 09:40.546
- [growling]

09:43.049 --> 09:44.250
AH!

09:44.317 --> 09:46.419
WHA-OH!
UGH!

09:46.485 --> 09:47.853
[booming explosion]

09:47.920 --> 09:48.988
[explosions]

09:49.055 --> 09:51.657
- WHA-HOO!

09:51.724 --> 09:52.725
[loud crash]

09:52.792 --> 09:55.328
[together]
SPRINGTIME!

09:55.394 --> 09:56.963
- THAT TIMMY TURNER
IS THE GREATEST KID

09:57.029 --> 09:58.197
I'VE EVER KNOWN.

09:58.264 --> 10:00.533
B-MINUS!

10:00.599 --> 10:03.202
- READY TO ADMIT YOUR MOM
HAS IT TOUGHER THAN YOU?

10:03.269 --> 10:04.904
- NO WAY.

10:04.971 --> 10:06.605
THIS DAY MAY HAVE BEEN CRAZY,

10:06.672 --> 10:08.574
BUT I KEPT IT ALL
UNDER CONTROL.

10:08.641 --> 10:10.409
I'M AN AWESOME MOM.

10:10.476 --> 10:12.311
[explosion]

10:12.378 --> 10:14.547
OH, NO, THE WASHING MACHINE
MUST HAVE OVERFLOWED.

10:14.613 --> 10:17.450
THE HOUSE IS RUINED.

10:17.516 --> 10:20.252
- OOH.

10:20.319 --> 10:22.555
- BEING A MOM
IS A TOTAL PAIN IN THE NECK.

10:22.621 --> 10:24.557
WANDA, I WAS WR--

10:24.623 --> 10:26.559
WRRRR--EGH.

10:26.625 --> 10:28.227
- CLUCK-CLUCK, CHICKEN BOY.

10:28.294 --> 10:29.428
- I WAS WRONG.

10:29.495 --> 10:30.396
YOU WIN.

10:30.463 --> 10:31.597
GO AHEAD.

10:31.664 --> 10:33.199
TAKE A WAY YOUR MAGIC
FOR A WEEK.

10:33.265 --> 10:34.667
- AW, TIMMY.

10:34.734 --> 10:36.936
I'M NOT GONNA TAKE AWAY
MY MAGIC.

10:37.003 --> 10:39.305
I JUST WANTED YOU TO LEARN
ABOUT HOW HARD IT IS

10:39.372 --> 10:40.539
BEING A MOM.

10:40.606 --> 10:42.541
- WELL, I DID,
BUT I BET MY MOM

10:42.608 --> 10:44.377
HAD A PRETTY TOUGH TIME
BEING ME TOO.

10:44.443 --> 10:46.746
[horn honking]

10:46.812 --> 10:48.647
UH, HI, TIMMY.

10:48.714 --> 10:49.749
HOW WAS YOUR DAY?

10:49.815 --> 10:52.184
- WELL, MOM...

10:52.251 --> 10:54.286
I SPENT MY DAY
DANCING AND SINGING.

10:54.353 --> 10:55.888
I BRAIDED TRIXIE'S HAIR

10:55.955 --> 10:58.624
AND GOT A B-MINUS
FROM MR. CROCKER.

10:58.691 --> 11:01.293
- GEE, THAT SOUNDS GREAT.

11:01.360 --> 11:02.261
- ARE YOU KIDDING?

11:02.328 --> 11:03.529
IT WAS TERRIBLE.

11:03.596 --> 11:05.664
THOSE PEOPLE ARE BANANAS.

11:05.731 --> 11:08.567
[together]
SPRINGTIME!

11:08.634 --> 11:10.870
- WELL, NOW I UNDERSTAND TIMMY
PERFECTLY.

11:10.936 --> 11:13.906
HE'S SO WELL-ADJUSTED COMPARED
TO THOSE OTHER KIDS,

11:13.973 --> 11:16.709
AND THAT MEANS
I'M A GREAT PARENT.

11:16.776 --> 11:18.244
I'M GOING TO CLOSE
MY EYES AGAIN,

11:18.310 --> 11:19.545
AND WHEN I OPEN THEM,

11:19.612 --> 11:21.647
I'LL STOP PRETENDING
TO BE TIMMY.

11:21.714 --> 11:22.982
I'M MOM AGAIN.

11:23.049 --> 11:23.983
I'M MOM AGAIN.

11:24.050 --> 11:25.384
I'M MOM AGAIN.

11:25.451 --> 11:26.852
[chimes]

11:26.919 --> 11:28.187
[zapping noise]

11:32.958 --> 11:34.026
HEY!

11:34.093 --> 11:35.795
WHAT HAPPENED TO THE HOUSE?

11:35.861 --> 11:37.229
- I'LL HELP YOU CLEAN IT UP,
MOM.

11:37.296 --> 11:38.931
- OH, THAT'S SWEET, TIMMY.

11:38.998 --> 11:40.966
BUT I'VE GOT IT UNDER CONTROL.

11:41.033 --> 11:42.601
MOM POWERS, ACTIVATE.

11:42.668 --> 11:45.971
SHAPE OF A CLEANING TORNADO.

11:46.038 --> 11:48.941
[whirling whistle noise]

11:51.444 --> 11:54.113
- WOW, YOU'RE, LIKE, MAGIC.

11:54.180 --> 11:57.116
- OH, THAT'S WHAT BEING A MOM
IS ALL ABOUT.

11:57.183 --> 11:59.618
- HI, HONEY, I'M HOME.

11:59.685 --> 12:02.721
HOW ABOUT ANOTHER DISTURBING
EUROPEAN-STYLE KISS?

12:02.788 --> 12:04.123
[smooching and blabbering]

12:04.190 --> 12:05.491
- WANT TO BORROW THE EEL?

12:05.558 --> 12:08.494
- I'VE DONE WELL WITH YOU,
TIMMY.

12:08.561 --> 12:11.497
- DEH!
THERE'S THAT SPARK.

12:11.564 --> 12:12.631
EUROPE HURTS MY LIPS.

12:31.417 --> 12:32.618
- HA-HA!

12:32.685 --> 12:35.488
MY NEW INVENTION
WILL REARRANGE MY MOLECULES

12:35.554 --> 12:36.722
AND BEAM ME DIRECTLY TO...

12:36.789 --> 12:38.057
FAIRY WORLD!

12:38.124 --> 12:39.592
THE PRIME HUNTING GROUND...

12:39.658 --> 12:43.095
FOR FAIRIES!

12:43.162 --> 12:45.431
[zapping noise]

12:45.498 --> 12:48.667
- OH, DENZEL,
WHAT'S BECOME OF YOU?

12:48.734 --> 12:49.835
- ISN'T IT OBVIOUS?

12:49.902 --> 12:51.904
I'M A HIDEOUS GOO MONSTER.

12:51.971 --> 12:53.539
- I'M TALKING ABOUT YOUR LIFE.

12:53.606 --> 12:55.341
YOU'RE NOTHING BUT A CRACKPOT

12:55.407 --> 12:59.612
WHO WASTES ALL HIS TIME
CHASING FAIRIES.

12:59.678 --> 13:00.613
- OOH!
OW!

13:00.679 --> 13:01.580
OW!
MY EYE!

13:01.647 --> 13:03.749
[shouting]

13:05.284 --> 13:06.318
[buzzing]

13:06.385 --> 13:09.788
[zapping noise]

13:09.855 --> 13:11.757
FREEZE, YOU CRAZY WITCH!

13:11.824 --> 13:13.559
[zapping noise]

13:13.626 --> 13:14.960
AH!

13:15.027 --> 13:16.662
[explosion]

13:16.729 --> 13:19.031
OH, MAYBE
THE FROZEN OLD KOOK'S RIGHT.

13:19.098 --> 13:20.466
MY OBSESSION WITH...
FAIRIES!

13:20.533 --> 13:22.601
HAS YIELDED NOTHING
BUT DISASTER.

13:22.668 --> 13:24.770
THERE'S ONLY ONE SANE THING
TO DO:

13:24.837 --> 13:26.939
FIND ANOTHER CRAZY OBSESSION.

13:27.006 --> 13:29.675
LET'S GO TO THE WHEEL
OF DESTINY.

13:29.742 --> 13:32.278
ONE SPIN AWAY
FROM A WHOLE NEW LIFE.

13:34.446 --> 13:35.681
MAYBE I SHOULD SHOOT
FOR SOMETHING

13:35.748 --> 13:36.782
A LITTLE MORE REALISTIC.

13:36.849 --> 13:39.285
COME ON, UNICORNS!

13:39.351 --> 13:40.519
LEPRECHAUNS?

13:40.586 --> 13:41.654
THAT'S IT!

13:41.720 --> 13:43.222
NOT ONLY ARE THEY
MAGICAL CREATURES,

13:43.289 --> 13:44.690
BUT THEY CAN'T FLY,
SO THEY'LL BE EASIER

13:44.757 --> 13:46.258
TO CATCH THAN...
FAIRIES!

13:46.325 --> 13:51.163
PLUS THEY HAVE POTS OF GOLD,
WHICH I CAN USE TO BUY STUFF.

13:51.230 --> 13:52.164
UGH!

13:52.231 --> 13:54.934
LIKE A BETTER WHEEL OF DESTINY.

13:55.000 --> 13:58.504
ACCORDING TO LEPRECHAPEDIA,
LEPRECHAUNS LIVE IN IRELAND.

13:58.571 --> 14:00.806
SINCE I CAN'T AFFORD TO GO THERE
ON A TEACHER'S SALARY,

14:00.873 --> 14:02.274
I'LL HAVE TO SETTLE
FOR LITTLE IRELAND

14:02.341 --> 14:03.976
IN DOWNTOWN DIMMSDALE.

14:04.043 --> 14:05.844
TO THE UNSUSPECTING VAN!

14:07.580 --> 14:11.417
[engine grinding]

14:11.483 --> 14:14.653
TO THE UNSUSPECTING
JUMPER CABLES!

14:14.720 --> 14:17.690
[bagpipe music]

14:17.756 --> 14:20.893
♪ ♪

14:20.960 --> 14:23.696
- COSMO, WHAT ARE WE DOING
IN LITTLE IRELAND?

14:23.762 --> 14:26.198
I SAID, "I WISH,"
NOT "I-RISH."

14:26.265 --> 14:27.967
- OOH, BUT CAN WE STAY?

14:28.033 --> 14:30.035
THEY'RE CELEBRATING
MY FAVORITE HOLIDAY,

14:30.102 --> 14:31.537
LEPRECHANUKA.

14:31.604 --> 14:34.740
- COSMO, THERE'S NO SUCH THING
AS LEPRECHANUKA.

14:34.807 --> 14:36.075
- DON'T LISTEN TO HER, TIMMY.

14:36.141 --> 14:38.043
ON THE EIGHTH DAY
OF LEPRECHANUKA,

14:38.110 --> 14:40.913
THE GREAT POTATO RISES OUT OF
THE FOUR-LEAF CLOVER FIELD

14:40.980 --> 14:45.684
WITH CHOCOLATE COINS AND
POTATO DREIDELS FOR EVERYONE.

14:45.751 --> 14:47.720
- OH, LITTLE IRELAND.

14:47.786 --> 14:49.622
EVERYTHING IS SO GREEN HERE,

14:49.688 --> 14:50.756
EVEN THE STOPLIGHTS.

14:50.823 --> 14:52.791
[chaotic crashing noises]

14:52.858 --> 14:54.526
WELL, TIME TO SET UP
MY STATE-OF-THE-ART

14:54.593 --> 14:55.861
LEPRECHAUN TRAP.

14:55.928 --> 14:57.296
NOW FOR THE BAIT.

14:57.363 --> 14:59.865
NO LEPRECHAUN CAN RESIST
MOTHER'S IRISH STEW.

14:59.932 --> 15:03.535
[dreamy chime sounds]

15:03.602 --> 15:05.237
- THEN THE GREAT POTATO
LOOKS IN THE MIRROR

15:05.304 --> 15:07.840
TO SEE IF HE'S THE FAIREST
POTATO OF THEM ALL.

15:07.906 --> 15:09.942
IF HE'S NOT, HE GIVES
THE HOTTER-LOOKING POTATO

15:10.009 --> 15:11.410
A POISON APPLE.

15:11.477 --> 15:13.946
- UH, LEPRECHANUKA SOUNDS
KIND OF LAME, COSMO.

15:14.013 --> 15:15.247
- WHAT IF I TOLD YOU
LEPRECHANUKA

15:15.314 --> 15:17.149
WAS A SCHOOL HOLIDAY?

15:17.216 --> 15:20.886
- I LOVE LEPRECHANUKA.

15:20.953 --> 15:22.054
- MM.

15:22.121 --> 15:23.689
I SMELL STEW.

15:23.756 --> 15:26.058
EITHER THAT OR IT'S
THE GREAT POTATO'S AFTERSHAVE.

15:28.227 --> 15:29.295
[snapping sound]

15:29.361 --> 15:30.329
- GAH!

15:30.396 --> 15:32.598
- EUREKA!
I CAPTURED A LEPRECHAUN!

15:32.665 --> 15:34.967
WAIT, MAYBE I SHOULD SAY
SOMETHING MORE IRISH.

15:35.034 --> 15:36.435
SHIVER ME TIMBERS!

15:36.502 --> 15:38.504
- GAH!
- YOU'RE MINE, LEPRECHAUN.

15:38.570 --> 15:40.706
NOW, GIVE ME MY POT OF GOLD.

15:40.773 --> 15:42.141
- I DON'T HAVE ONE.

15:42.207 --> 15:44.143
BUT I DO HAVE A STORY
ABOUT HOW THE GREAT POTATO

15:44.209 --> 15:45.844
ONCE STOPPED A WOLF
FROM BLOWING DOWN A HOUSE

15:45.911 --> 15:47.279
MADE OF STRING FRIES.

15:47.346 --> 15:49.148
- LOOK, THE RULE IS,
IF YOU CATCH A LEPRECHAUN,

15:49.214 --> 15:50.949
HE HAS TO GIVE YOU HIS GOLD.

15:51.016 --> 15:52.418
SO FORK IT OVER!

15:52.484 --> 15:55.321
- WELL, IF THAT'S THE RULE.

15:55.387 --> 15:56.588
- MISSION ACCOMPLISHED.

15:56.655 --> 15:58.023
NOW THAT I HAVE YOUR GOLD,

15:58.090 --> 15:59.858
TAKE A HIKE, MCMORON.

15:59.925 --> 16:01.460
- COSMO, WHERE WERE YOU?

16:01.527 --> 16:03.796
YOU MISSED
THE POTATO-SCULPTING CONTEST.

16:03.862 --> 16:07.032
- POOF WON FIRST PRIZE
WITH HIS BATTLE OF GETTYSBURG.

16:07.099 --> 16:08.300
- POOF-POOF!

16:08.367 --> 16:09.868
[booming splat]

16:09.935 --> 16:12.004
- SORRY, BUT I GOT CAPTURED
BY MR. CROCKER,

16:12.071 --> 16:13.305
WHO THOUGHT I WAS A LEPRECHAUN,

16:13.372 --> 16:14.740
AND MADE ME GIVE HIM
A POT OF GOLD.

16:14.807 --> 16:15.741
OOH!

16:15.808 --> 16:18.777
POTATO SOLDIERS.

16:18.844 --> 16:20.679
- OH.
WHAT?

16:20.746 --> 16:23.349
COSMO, FAIRIES AREN'T ALLOWED
TO POOF OFF MONEY.

16:23.415 --> 16:25.317
WHERE'D YOU GET A POT OF GOLD?

16:25.384 --> 16:28.053
- FROM SOME LEPRECHAUNS.
DUH.

16:28.120 --> 16:29.288
- WHICH ONES?

16:29.355 --> 16:31.223
SOME OF THEM CAN BE REALLY
DANGEROUS.

16:31.290 --> 16:32.758
- HA-HA, COME ON.

16:32.825 --> 16:34.660
AREN'T THEY ALL JUST HARMLESS
LITTLE GREEN TWERPS

16:34.727 --> 16:36.261
WHO SELL SOAP ON TV?

16:36.328 --> 16:37.196
UGH!

16:37.262 --> 16:38.430
- OH, NO!

16:38.497 --> 16:40.265
IT'S THE MCPUNCHY BROTHERS--

16:40.332 --> 16:43.001
LUCKY, GREENY, AND BIG DAVE,

16:43.068 --> 16:46.105
THE TOUGHEST, MEANEST
LEPRECHAUNS EVER.

16:46.171 --> 16:47.740
- WHOA,
THEY'RE NOT JUST LEPRECHAUNS.

16:47.806 --> 16:49.575
THEY'RE LEPRE-CONVICTS.

16:49.641 --> 16:51.176
- THAT'S RIGHT, BUCKO.

16:51.243 --> 16:53.412
THEY SENT US TO JAIL
'CAUSE OF THE TERRIBLE THINGS

16:53.479 --> 16:55.814
WE DID TO THE LAST THIEF
WHO TOOK OUR GOLD.

16:55.881 --> 16:58.717
- AND WE BUSTED OUT 'CAUSE OUR
GOLD'S BEEN STOLEN AGAIN,

16:58.784 --> 17:02.187
BY A WEE-BRAINED LADDIE
NAMED COSMO-OO.

17:02.254 --> 17:04.189
- HOW DO YOU KNOW
IT WAS IT COSMO-OO?

17:04.256 --> 17:05.424
- HE LEFT A NOTE.

17:07.559 --> 17:08.993
- YOU LEFT A NOTE?

17:09.060 --> 17:12.231
- IT'S CALLED MANNERS, WANDA.
LOOK IT UP.

17:12.297 --> 17:13.198
- THEY'RE FAIRIES.

17:13.265 --> 17:14.867
GRAB THEIR WANDS.

17:18.237 --> 17:20.305
- NOW, GIVE US BACK
OUR POT OF GOLD.

17:20.372 --> 17:21.573
- HE DOESN'T HAVE IT ANYMORE.

17:21.640 --> 17:23.442
A GUY NAMED MR. CROCKER HAS IT.

17:23.509 --> 17:24.943
AND I CAN TAKE YOU TO HIM.

17:25.010 --> 17:26.145
- LUCKY, GREENY,

17:26.211 --> 17:28.247
TAKE THE PINK-HAIRED LASS
AND THE WEE ONE

17:28.313 --> 17:30.382
BACK TO IRELAND
FOR SAFE KEEPING.

17:30.449 --> 17:32.785
I'LL GO WITH THE BUCKTOOTHED LAD
AND HIS FRIEND

17:32.851 --> 17:35.454
TO SEE THIS MR. CROCKER,
EYA-ER-ERGH.

17:35.521 --> 17:37.556
- SAVE US, COSMO.

17:37.623 --> 17:38.924
- NO-HO-HO-HO-HO!

17:38.991 --> 17:40.492
NO-HO-HO,
TIMMY,

17:40.559 --> 17:42.494
WE GOT TO GET POOF AND WANDA
BACK.

17:42.561 --> 17:44.430
SHE HAS TO PAY FOR LUNCH.

17:44.496 --> 17:45.731
- DON'T WORRY, COSMO.

17:45.798 --> 17:47.566
WE JUST HAVE TO GET THAT GOLD
FROM MR. CROCKER

17:47.633 --> 17:49.134
BEFORE HE SPENDS ANY OF IT.

17:49.201 --> 17:51.503
- I'VE SPENT ALL OF IT!

17:51.570 --> 17:52.671
NOW TO LOAD THIS STUFF

17:52.738 --> 17:55.641
INTO MY NEW TRICKED-OUT
TALKING CAR.

17:55.707 --> 17:57.276
THIS IS THE BEST DAY EVER,

17:57.342 --> 17:59.344
TAKING CAR THAT OBEYS
MY EVERY COMMAND.

17:59.411 --> 18:00.345
MAKE ME A MILKSHAKE.

18:00.412 --> 18:02.181
- ACTIVATING AIRBAGS.

18:02.247 --> 18:03.315
- WHAT?
GAH!

18:03.382 --> 18:04.483
GUH!

18:04.550 --> 18:05.684
TURNER?

18:05.751 --> 18:07.553
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
WITH MY LEPRECHAUN?

18:07.619 --> 18:09.054
HE'S CLEANED OUT,
JUST SO YOU KNOW.

18:09.121 --> 18:11.790
- MR. CROCKER, YOU'VE GOT
TO GIVE BACK THAT GOLD.

18:11.857 --> 18:13.025
- WHO'S GONNA MAKE ME?

18:13.091 --> 18:15.093
YOU AND YOUR WIMPY
LITTLE LEPRECHAUN?

18:15.160 --> 18:16.728
[laughing]
[heavy stomping]

18:16.795 --> 18:18.730
- GUESS AGAIN, LADDIE.

18:20.599 --> 18:21.700
- AH!

18:21.767 --> 18:23.669
TIME FOR A QUICK GETAWAY,
TALKING CAR.

18:23.735 --> 18:26.038
- MAKING GETAWAY NOW.

18:26.104 --> 18:27.306
- I MEANT WITH ME!

18:27.372 --> 18:28.807
BRING BACK MY STUFF.

18:28.874 --> 18:30.108
AH!

18:30.175 --> 18:31.844
- YOU'VE GOT TILL THE END
OF LEPRECHANUKA

18:31.910 --> 18:34.079
TO GET ME POT OF GOLD BACK.

18:34.146 --> 18:36.615
- WAIT, LEPRECHANUKA'S
A REAL HOLIDAY?

18:36.682 --> 18:38.050
- OF COURSE IT'S REAL.

18:38.116 --> 18:40.752
AND IT ENDS WHEN THE LAST BIT
OF IRISH STEW

18:40.819 --> 18:42.554
DRIPS THROUGH THIS HOURGLASS.

18:42.621 --> 18:44.122
[mumbling indistinctly]

18:44.189 --> 18:45.824
JUST GET ME POT OF GOLD.

18:45.891 --> 18:47.192
UNTIL YOU DO,

18:47.259 --> 18:49.127
I'LL BE TAKING
THIS WHEEL OF DESTINY

18:49.194 --> 18:51.897
AS COLLATERAL...LE-LA-LE-LE-UH.

18:51.964 --> 18:53.031
[engine revving]

18:53.098 --> 18:54.900
- PLEASE, NOT MY WHEEL
OF DESTINY.

18:54.967 --> 18:57.102
TAKE THE RUBY TOILET INSTEAD.

18:57.169 --> 18:58.437
- WE GOT TO GET
THE MCPUNCHY BROTHERS

18:58.504 --> 18:59.838
ANOTHER POT OF GOLD.

18:59.905 --> 19:00.873
- HAVE NO FEAR.

19:00.939 --> 19:03.375
I HAVE A PLAN...NE-NESH-HE-NE.

19:03.442 --> 19:06.411
[rousing orchestral music]

19:06.478 --> 19:15.254
♪ ♪

19:15.320 --> 19:16.889
- ALL WE NEED
ARE THREE PERFECT TENS,

19:16.955 --> 19:18.490
AND WE'LL WIN THE GOLD MEDAL.

19:18.557 --> 19:20.359
- TEN.

19:20.425 --> 19:21.994
- TEN

19:22.060 --> 19:24.463
- "F"!

19:24.530 --> 19:26.331
SORRY, FORCE OF HABIT.

19:26.398 --> 19:28.534
WE'LL JUST MINE OUR OWN GOLD.

19:28.600 --> 19:31.703
- OKAY, BUT BE ON THE LOOKOUT
FOR EIGHT FAIRYTALE DWARVES.

19:31.770 --> 19:33.372
- I THOUGHT THERE WERE
ONLY SEVEN.

19:33.438 --> 19:36.909
- NO, EVERYONE ALWAYS FORGETS
THE EIGHTH DWARF, CRAZY.

19:36.975 --> 19:39.278
[dwarves shouting]

19:39.344 --> 19:40.546
- DAH!

19:40.612 --> 19:42.414
- [laughing crazily]

19:42.481 --> 19:44.082
- AH!

19:44.149 --> 19:45.250
- NOTE TO SELF:

19:45.317 --> 19:47.252
TAKE DWARVES OFF
THE WHEEL OF DESTINY.

19:47.319 --> 19:48.921
- GAH!
OH-HO, NO!

19:48.987 --> 19:50.389
- AH!

19:50.455 --> 19:51.957
[descending whistle]

19:52.024 --> 19:53.425
- WELL, LADDIES,

19:53.492 --> 19:56.795
I STILL DON'T HAVE THAT
MCPUNCHY FAMILY POT OF GOLD,

19:56.862 --> 20:01.433
WHICH MEANS YOU'RE ALL GETTING
BOILED LIKE A CABBAGE--AG-ARGH.

20:03.335 --> 20:05.037
- I GOT TO GET OUT OF HERE.

20:05.103 --> 20:06.772
TALKING CAR, COME AND GET ME.

20:06.838 --> 20:07.839
- HOP IN.

20:07.906 --> 20:09.141
- GAH!

20:09.207 --> 20:12.511
[engine revving]

20:12.578 --> 20:14.012
- COME ON, COSMO,

20:14.079 --> 20:15.914
HE'LL LEAD US
TO WANDA AND POOF.

20:15.981 --> 20:17.683
WHO KNOWS WHAT HORRIBLE
IRISH TORTURE

20:17.749 --> 20:19.117
THEY'RE BEING PUT THROUGH?

20:19.184 --> 20:22.054
[upbeat instrumental music]

20:23.388 --> 20:24.856
- [exclaiming throatily]

20:24.923 --> 20:27.626
OH, I LOVE IRELAND, POOF.

20:27.693 --> 20:30.562
THERE'S ALL THE MARSHMALLOW
CEREAL YOU CAN EAT,

20:30.629 --> 20:34.166
AND DEODORANT SOAP
GROWS ON TREES.

20:34.232 --> 20:36.068
[rock music]

20:36.134 --> 20:37.903
- LUCKY, GREENY,

20:37.970 --> 20:41.540
FIRE UP THE CABBAGE BOILER...
[grumbling]

20:41.607 --> 20:43.008
- I WOULD IF I COULD FIND IT.

20:43.075 --> 20:46.345
BUT IT'S GREEN LIKE EVERYTHING
ELSE AROUND HERE.

20:46.411 --> 20:48.480
[jubilant fanfare]

20:48.547 --> 20:49.748
[loud thud]

20:49.815 --> 20:51.617
- COSMO!
- DADDA!

20:51.683 --> 20:52.884
- FAIRIES?

20:52.951 --> 20:54.653
AND JUST WHEN I'D GIVEN UP
CHASING THEM.

20:54.720 --> 20:55.954
THAT'S SO NOT FAIR.

20:56.021 --> 20:57.689
- I REALLY MISSED YOU GUYS.

20:57.756 --> 21:00.025
- WE MISSED YOU TOO, COSMO.

21:00.092 --> 21:03.128
NOW LET'S GET OUT OF HERE
BEFORE THE MCPUNCHYS COME TO.

21:03.195 --> 21:07.633
- YOU'RE A WEE BIT TOO LATE,
LASSIE.

21:07.699 --> 21:08.700
- AH!

21:08.767 --> 21:10.402
- DAH!

21:12.771 --> 21:14.373
[loud snap]

21:14.439 --> 21:15.841
- DON'T WORRY, GUYS.

21:15.907 --> 21:18.677
BOILING PEOPLE ON LEPRECHANUKA
IS A BIG NO-NO.

21:18.744 --> 21:21.046
THE GREAT POTATO
WILL NEVER LET THIS HAPPEN.

21:21.113 --> 21:23.248
- COSMO, ONCE AND FOR ALL,

21:23.315 --> 21:25.751
THERE'S NO SUCH THING
AS THE GREAT POTATO.

21:25.817 --> 21:27.452
[heavy rumbling]

21:27.519 --> 21:30.522
- HAPPY LEPRECHANUKA,
EVERYBODY.

21:30.589 --> 21:33.525
AND STOP BOILING THOSE PEOPLE
AT ONCE.

21:33.592 --> 21:34.893
- [together] SAINTS ALIVE.

21:34.960 --> 21:37.295
IT'S THE GREAT POTATO.

21:37.362 --> 21:39.197
- NO WAY.
HE'S REAL?

21:39.264 --> 21:40.499
- ISN'T HE AWESOME, TIMMY?

21:40.565 --> 21:42.768
EXCEPT AT MIDNIGHT HE TURNS BACK
INTO A PUMPKIN.

21:42.834 --> 21:45.203
- HEAR ME, MCPUNCHY BROTHERS.

21:45.270 --> 21:47.839
FREE COSMO AND HIS FRIENDS
AT ONCE,

21:47.906 --> 21:51.043
OR SUFFER MY STARCHY WRATH.

21:51.109 --> 21:52.177
- EEH!

21:52.244 --> 21:53.945
RIGHT AWAY, GREAT POTATO.

21:54.012 --> 21:56.014
LUCKY, GREENY, UNTIE THEM.

21:56.081 --> 21:58.650
AND GIVE THE FAIRIES BACK
THEIR WANDS.

21:58.717 --> 21:59.751
- WAIT A MINUTE.

21:59.818 --> 22:01.219
EVEN THE STUPID LEPRECHAUN
WAS A...

22:01.286 --> 22:02.220
FAIRY?

22:02.287 --> 22:04.289
THAT'S EVEN MORE SO NOT FAIR.

22:04.356 --> 22:05.657
- THANKS, GREAT POTATO.

22:05.724 --> 22:08.026
WELL, I GUESS WE'LL BE HEADING
BACK HOME.

22:08.093 --> 22:09.728
SORRY ABOUT YOUR GOLD.

22:09.795 --> 22:11.763
- IT WASN'T THE GOLD
WE CARED ABOUT, LAD.

22:11.830 --> 22:13.999
WE JUST WANTED THE POT BACK.

22:14.066 --> 22:15.967
- IT'S A MCPUNCHY FAMILY
HEIRLOOM.

22:16.034 --> 22:17.135
- HE'S STILL GOT THE POT.

22:17.202 --> 22:18.537
IT'S IN MY TRUNK.

22:18.603 --> 22:19.938
- DON'T TELL THEM THAT.

22:20.005 --> 22:21.907
I WAS GONNA USE IT
AS A PLANTER.

22:21.973 --> 22:23.275
[beep]

22:23.341 --> 22:25.977
CURSE YOU, STUPID TALKING CAR.

22:26.044 --> 22:27.079
HA!

22:27.145 --> 22:29.181
UGH!
DAH!

22:29.247 --> 22:31.149
- NOW LET'S GO HOME.

22:31.216 --> 22:33.151
- TAKE US TO DIMMSDALE,
TALKING CAR.

22:33.218 --> 22:35.420
- ACTIVATING EJECTOR SEAT.

22:35.487 --> 22:36.421
AH!

22:36.488 --> 22:38.056
[screaming]

22:38.123 --> 22:39.324
UGH!

22:39.391 --> 22:41.493
WELL, THE LEPRECHAUN THING
WAS A TOTAL BUST.

22:41.560 --> 22:43.829
SO IT'S BACK
TO THE WHEEL OF DESTINY.

22:46.431 --> 22:48.100
DWARVES?
NO WAY!

22:48.166 --> 22:49.835
I'M NOT GOING BACK TO CRAZY.

22:49.901 --> 22:52.137
- YOU'RE ALREADY THERE,
YOU NUMBSKULL.

22:52.204 --> 22:53.672
- OH, JUST MY LUCK.

22:53.739 --> 22:55.407
MOTHER'S VOCAL CORDS
HAVE THAWED OUT.

22:57.309 --> 22:58.310
FAIRIES!

22:58.376 --> 22:59.678
LOOKS LIKE WE HAVE A WINNER!

22:59.745 --> 23:01.379
- YOU CRACKPOT!

23:01.446 --> 23:03.048
EEH!
HELP, TALKING CAR.

23:03.115 --> 23:04.049
GET ME OUT OF HERE.

23:04.116 --> 23:05.217
AH!
GUH-GEH.

23:05.283 --> 23:07.486
WELL, AT LEAST IT'S GOOD
TO HAVE FRIENDS.

23:07.552 --> 23:08.754
[descending whistle]

23:08.820 --> 23:12.290
- HAPPY LEPRECHANUKA,
EVERYBODY.

